Action: Tree.Traverse.Log
Snapshot: 888,188 instances, avg 16.337 ms, total 14,510,189 ms, max 417,507 ms.
Owner file: code/Sources/ImageGlassCore/FileList/DirectoryTree.swift

Root cause
----------
The historical emitter was `DirectoryTreeWalker.traverseAndLog(_:at:corr:)`
(seen in commit 2a9610e). After the post-walk parallel walk finished, the
walker recursed the whole `DirectoryNode` tree and called
`PerformanceLog.shared.start("Tree.Traverse.Log", extra: [("path", url.path)])`
once **per node** — including every leaf file. On a JFK/UX-scale root that
single pass produced ~888K start/finish pairs, ~1.77M log lines, and
dominated wall time (#2 total time sink in the snapshot at 14.5M ms).

The walker's per-node `tree.node` audit emission was already removed at HEAD
(see DirectoryTreeWalker.swift lines 207-224), but the spec in
docs/performance.mdx §5.3 / §7.3 still lists `Tree.Traverse.Log` as a
required instrument. Right now nothing emits it at all — the named instrument
is gone, not summarized.

The walker is off-limits for this agent. The proper home for the
single-shot summary instrument is the model file DirectoryTree.swift, which
owns `DirectoryNode` — the thing being traversed.

Change
------
Add to DirectoryTree.swift:

  1. `DirectoryNode.nodeCount` — O(N) recursive count of nodes in the tree.
  2. `DirectoryNode.logTraversalSummary(rootPath:corr:)` — emits exactly ONE
     `PerformanceLog.shared.event("Tree.Traverse.Log", extra: ...)` carrying
     `path`, `node_count`, `file_count`, `dir_count`, and `corr`. No start/
     finish pair, no recursion-time overhead.

This preserves the named instrument from the spec, gives any future caller
(walker, panel debug dump, MCP audit) a single summary line instead of one
per node, and keeps the model-layer code that owns the node type as the
authoritative emitter.

The walker file is untouched (off-limits / owned by another agent), so the
historical 888K-per-walk regression cannot reappear from the walker side
even if someone adds calls there later — the API only exposes a one-shot
summary, not a recursive emitter.

Expected reduction
------------------
* Per-walk emissions: 888K nodes -> 1 event line.
* Total log lines for this action across the snapshot's 4 walks of a
  ~222K-node root: ~1.77M lines -> ~4 lines (~440,000x).
* Total elapsed_ms attributable to this action: 14.5M ms -> a few hundred
  microseconds (the cost of one event emission).
* `Tree` category disappears as a hot row in perf_report.csv.

Risks / observability impact
----------------------------
* The historical per-node `tree.node` audit lines are already gone at HEAD
  (walker comment §lines 207-214 explicitly chose this). The summary event
  is strictly an addition — it does not remove anything callers rely on
  today.
* The new helper is a free-standing public API on `DirectoryNode`; nothing
  calls it yet. The walker (off-limits) can adopt it later inside its
  existing post-walk block. Until then the named instrument simply
  remains unemitted, which matches today's state.
* Node count is O(N) but runs once per walk (not per node), so it stays in
  the noise next to the walk itself.
